-- Statement: CLOSE SYMMETRIC KEY
-- Grammar rule: closeSymmetricKeyStatement (TSql170.g)
-- Doc: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/t-sql/statements/close-symmetric-key-transact-sql

-- From TSql170.g:
closeSymmetricKeyStatement:
    ( SYMMETRIC KEY identifier )
    | ( ALL SYMMETRIC KEYS )
    ;

-- Note: The CLOSE keyword is consumed by the parent dispatcher rule (closeStatements).

-- From Microsoft docs:
CLOSE { SYMMETRIC KEY key_name | ALL SYMMETRIC KEYS }
